how dangerous are premature atrial contractions if they happen times a day i've been diagnosed as having pac's premature atrial contractions i've been told by my doctor that they're harmless and i ignored them when they were only happening a couple of times a day they are now becoming more frequent though more like times a day and it's starting to worry me should i be concerned thank you pacs are harmless and very common i have thousands of pvcs premature ventricular contraction daily you should go to your cardiologist and get your heart checked out to make sure there's no underlying cause for your pacs if everything's normal you have nothing to worry about triggers for my pvcs are caffeine alcohol and stress reduce or eliminate your caffeine and alcohol intake will definitely help Cardiac arrhythmia Premature ventricular contraction Atrial fibrillation Cardiology Antiarrhythmic agent Ventricular fibrillation Hypertrophic cardiomyopathy Arrhythmogenic right ventricular dysplasia Folic acid Myocardial infarction Anxiety Stroke Childbirth Amiodarone Anemia Urinary incontinence Tocopherol Hypoglycemia Atrial septal defect Electrocardiogram Flecainide Migraine Hypertension Implantable cardioverter-defibrillator Caffeine Sleep Polyvinyl chloride Atrial flutter Breastfeeding Cardiac stress test Mitral stenosis Wolff-Parkinson-White syndrome Cardiac cycle Bipolar disorder Fecal incontinence Insomnia Mitral regurgitation Cephalic disorder Tobacco smoking Alcohol Acute respiratory distress syndrome Alcoholism Transposition of the Great Arteries Warfarin Miscarriage Premature birth Short QT syndrome Psychosis Prostate cancer Blood pressure Medicine Schizophrenia Traumatic brain injury Vitamin C Adenosine Jugular venous pressure Tachycardia Atkins Nutritional Approach Asthma Infantilism Cardiac pacemaker Noonan syndrome Trazodone Cirrhosis 2004 Indian Ocean earthquake Osteoporosis Transient ischemic attack Clomipramine Defibrillator Angina Hormone replacement therapy (trans) T